gomodel:SYNGO_1177  a    owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment     "Rationale: In fig 2 the authors localize epsin 1 to presynaptic coated pits. In fig 3/4 they inject function blocking antibodies recognizing epsin 1 into the pre synapse.This leads to a massive reduction in the number of SVs following a 5 Hz 30 min stimulation. In fig. 4 they use EM to demonstrate a change in the morphology of clathrin-coated pits.\n\n10/10/2017 Pim\n- I have added Fig.6 to the referenced figures that show effect of anti-epsin antibodies.. Experimental description: by using the lamprey reticulospinal synapse as a model system" ;
        lego:modelstate  "production" ;
        dc:contributor   "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date          "2017-10-10" ;
        dc:title         "SYNGO_BP_1177" ;
        pav:providedBy   "https://syngo.vu.nl" .

